Name: Inside NU
Content: Here come the ‘Cats

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Las Vegas Bowl is just hours away. Get acquainted with who’s playing for both sides, plus how to watch and if Northwestern is favored.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Today’s injury report for Northwestern. 

Coco Azema, who has been in a walking boot all week, is officially out.

The surprise of the day: QB Brendan Sullivan, who started four games this season, is inactive. Could be a problem for NU if Ben Bryant gets hurt.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Yeah. 

This is insane.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern president Michael Schill was greeted with a mix of cheers and boos.

"It has been incredible to watch this team stack up win after win. They have inspired all of us — on campus, and around the world. They inspired us with their tenacy. This is what Wildcats do."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern AD Derrick Gragg speaking at Northwestern Alumni's pregame tailgate: "What more can we say about Coach Dave Braun?"

Also thanked fans for staying loyal, and praised the team.

"You're going to see, in a just few hours, what your team is capable of."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The grapes make an appearance in Vegas to close the 2023 season.

First time we're seeing purple-purple-purple since Ireland, which is well over a year ago.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Yeah. 

This is insane.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Most of our staffers project that the Wildcats will make it five straight bowl game wins by taking down Utah from Allegiant Stadium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Start off gameday right — with all our thoughts on Northwestern sports in the latest mailbag.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Per source, Northwestern will start Jordan Knox at LG in the Las Vegas Bowl in place of Josh Priebe, who entered the transfer portal.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Immensely clean. Best helmet of the year for NU's biggest game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun and Whittingham with the Las Vegas Bowl trophy, which they'll compete for tomorrow night.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on coaching NU : "To pretend that I've wrapped my head around it would be me blowing smoke.

On recruiting and managing the program: "The way that we move and operate is to ensure we retain those young men."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Gallagher on advice from Blake Gallagher on playing in a bowl: "He's someone I lean on every week. He watches the game every week, and gives me feedback.

Biggest advice was, "Business is business. But when it's time to have fun with your teammates and enjoy the city, do that."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on talking to Matt Entz and potentially asking him to join the Northwestern staff: "I'll keep those conversations private. He'll go outside his comfort zone, and I promise that USC is not inside Matt Entz's comfort zone."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said the "hardest thing" to navigate is scholarship numbers.

"I'm here to serve these guys, support these guys. That'll continue."

Said it's "okay" if players decide to leave, either via the NFL or portal.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun said that Pat Fitzgerald "did an incredible job" of allowing younger support staffers to have the chance to grow, and that he wants to sustain that.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun adds that it's a "great opportunity to explore." Said he's in favor of modeling field-to-sideline communication after the NFL.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant on how new in-helmet communication affects game flow: "I think we're pretty excited. We're excited to test that out, and I think it'll improve the game."

Gallagher adds NU will "try not to overdo it," but that they've used the helmet communication in their practices.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Noted Bryant as a prime example of bringing in " the right person" in adding players for NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on balancing recruiting with bowl prep: "Taking it one hour at a time... We're short-staffed right now, but there's not a single person in our organization that's making excuses..."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on leading NU in his final year: "There's so much maturity on this team. I've been so blessed to be around a great group of guys. I'm so happy this team brought me in and welcomed me with open arms."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the feeling of coaching a bowl game compared to being hired as DC at the beginning of the year: "It's incredibly special. This opportunity at Northwestern is a dream come true. Has it sunk in? It hasn't. I'm waking up each morning full of gratitude for the opportunity."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on carrying momentum in the postseason: "I've been so impressed with our team.. I've been so impressed with our practices back in Evanston, but I was most blown away with our Monday practice at Bishop Gorman."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on being named Newcomer Coach of the Year: "I was not aware, but everything that this team has achieved is a reflection of the character of this group.

"I was asked yesterday how we did this. It's the leadership."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryce Gallagher on his favorite part of Vegas: "The magic show. That was unbelievable, getting to spend time with my teammates and see some of the magic that Matt Franco was able to put on was an incredible experience."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun calls Utah an "incredibly formidable opponent."

Emphasizes that he views Utah as a model of a program that's built off of "team football, physicality and fundamentals."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun said those extra three weeks together and the extra game was an added motivation through the final weeks of the season.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "This is an incredible opportunity. It starts with the opportunity that we've gotten to have additional weeks of practice, with a special group of young men.

"An opportunity to continue a season with an incredible group of people. You couldn't ask for anything more."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern side speaking now.

David Braun in his openining statement: "This has been an incredible experience for our staff, our families. Unbelievable week so far.

"Something we'll remember for a long, long time."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Whittingham on what's stood out about Northwestern: "Toughness. Offensive line's impressive. It all starts up front. Good quarterback, receiver that's caught a lot of balls...

Said he sees a "lot of similar traits between the two programs."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Whittingham on whether Northwestern's 2018 Holiday Bowl win adds motivation: "I don't think there's extra motivation. That was so many years ago, no one on this roster was involved."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Kyle Whittingham in his opening statement: "No strangers to the Vegas Bowl. Excited to have the opportunity to play a great Northwestern team.

Added that "both teams faced a lot of adversity this year in their own way."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kicking off coverage here from Allegiant Stadium! Ben Bryant, Bryce Gallagher and David Braun set to speak to the media.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Pound the Talk episodes from on the road are simply the best.

Name: Inside NU
Content: To take down Utah, Northwestern should need to stick to its familiar keys:

Name: Inside NU
Content: A bowl rematch with the Utes brings new questions.  offers some more insight on Utah, and what Northwestern can expect tomorrow night:

Name: Inside NU
Content: A double-digit comeback win means it’s time for a more macro look at the Wildcats. Here are three takeaways from Northwestern women’s basketball’s latest victory:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Viva Las Vegas

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern’s rebounding success was not only a big reason why it prevailed over Arizona State, but also a sign in the right direction. That, and more from the Wildcats’ impressive night in Phoenix:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Get acquainted with the 15 latest Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern secured its second straight victory against Temple, thanks to second-half heroics from Melannie Daley.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 72, Temple 68

The 'Cats seemed outplayed at first but headlined by Melannie Daley, they were unstoppable in the second half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 70-66 with just eight seconds left and Temple has two free throws.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 'Cats up 68-61 with 30 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: At this point, if Melannie Daley is going to shoot just let her.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats are up 64-54 with 04:27 left. Daley has scored 10 points this quarter and 14 straight NU points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Melannie Daley is putting on a show. That is all.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley just scored another six points, making for 10 straight points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Put the team on your back Melannie Daley. Two free throws and a layup in 35 seconds make it 49-45 headed into the last quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Back even at 45.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NU had its biggest lead of the day at 42-37.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Tied back at 14 through four minutes in the third.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And just like that, Northwestern is ahead 32-30 off baskets from Walsh, Mott and Daley.

Name: Inside NU
Content: In the final minutes, three baskets brought the 'Cats to 30-26 headed into the half. NU is keeping this one close.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lau gets the rebound and sprints down court to make it 28-21.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Walsh breaks through the nearly five-minute drought to make it 28-19.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 28-17 with five minutes left in the second quarter. Paige Mott has scored the 'Cats' lone basket.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With four seconds left a three gives Temple a 18-15 lead headed into the second quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Fueled by a 7-point out of a timeout, the 'Cats eventually evened the score at 15 with a minute left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Temple leads Northwestern 13-5. The teams were trading basket, but the Owls are currently riding an 11-point run.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern women's basketball will look for two straight wins before the holiday break this morning. Follow along for updates.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats looked more like the Phoenix Suns in the Footprint Center, crushing Arizona State.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 65, Arizona State 46

The Wildcats stood on business out in Phoenix, throttling the Sun Devils. Boo Buie led NU with 22 points, while Ty Berry collected a double-double.

The Sun Devils shot just 31% from the floor in the Footprint Center.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry has his first double-double since last year at Indiana with 12 points and 10 rebounds!

Name: Inside NU
Content: With just 3:04 left, Northwestern is coasting 61-42. The 'Cats haven't been trailing since it was 2-0 Sun Devils. Flat out dominant showing.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie goes iso and makes a floater to get to 20 points. The most amazing thing is that he never felt fully dominant.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Have to say, appreciate the "U of A" chants whenever Arizona State is at the line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer breaks the ice in the second half via a free throw. He's up to 14 now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chris Collins calls timeout, but Northwestern is still boatracing Arizona State 56-39. To be fair, the Sun Devils are outscoring the Wildcats 26-20 in the second half, but there's just 7:19 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Martinelli's had a quietly good night for NU. Six points, three rebounds and two assists off the bench.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Martinelli lays it in, and the lead has ballooned back to 21 for Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie now has four threes! Up to 14 points on the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jose Perez has hit four free throws, but it's still a 44-28 lead for the 'Cats with 12:12 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins makes a layup over a defender, but Langborg answers right away with a three. Those are his first points of the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miller makes two free throws, and Arizona State has cut the lead to inside of 20.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats have just five points in this whole second half, and Barnhizer hasn't scored yet. But so far, it hasn't been of consequence.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We have reached College Football playoff discourse territory because this game is so lopsided.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brooks Barnhizer, Boo Buie and Ty Berry is what we thought this trio would be

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer can't get the shot off, and it's the under-16. Northwestern hanging on to a 20-point lead with a 41-21 advantage.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Akil Watson fights through contact to draw an and-one, making the free throw.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie making it rain in Phoenix! He hits his third three of the evening, and it's still a 23-point lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry hits Nicholson, who uses a fake and then lays it in off the glass.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miller converts a corner three to get the scoring started in the final 20.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALF: Northwestern 36, Arizona State 13

Yeah, you read that right. An unreal showing on both sides in the first 20 minutes for NU.

Brooks Barnhizer has 13, while Ty Berry has added nine of his own.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats force an ASU turnover, and Barnhizer makes a second-chance layup. That ends an unreal first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miller makes one of two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miller will shoot two after a foul on Berry.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Good defense from Barnhizer to force a jump ball. Pretty much everything swaying purple.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer works a flurry of moves and then drills a falling jumper. It's a 22-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie drops it off to Hunger, who's good. 32-12 Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie splashes a deep straightaway three, and Northwestern leads ASU by 18.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
We've hit the under-8, and Northwestern leads Arizona State 27-12.

The 'Cats are shooting 50% and have seen big contributions from Brooks Barnhizer and Ty Berry. Luke Hunger has also been impactful with Matt Nicholson/Blake Preston in foul trouble.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hunger snares the miss from Berry and lays it in. He's playing at a high level right now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Selebangue makes a layup, which is just the fifth FG for ASU. The first half is 75% over.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer gets the steal and feeds Berry, who hits another trey! The Wildcats have their biggest lead of the night at 15, and No. 3 has nine.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer swishes a crossover elbow jumper, and he's got nine points already.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A good dish from Langborg hits Hunger, who makes the layup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant Selebangue draws contact on Luke Hunger but misses both free throws. The two sides are 1-for-7 from the line (!!)

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg throws it right to the ASU bench, and he now has two turnovers. The 'Cats are up to five, but still lead 18-10.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson bumps Collins, and now he too has two fouls.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brycen Jong drills a corner three for ASU following the pause, and Blake Preston has already committed his second foul.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry splashes a three, and ASU is forced to call timeout. The Wildcats lead by 11 and have made their last four shots.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Neal sinks a three, but Nick Martinelli answers with an impressive fake and bank shot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer attacks, spins and makes a tough shot. Northwestern now leads by nine with 11:30 to go in the first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie breaks the scoring lull with a friendly roll. 'Cats up 11-4.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Is the roof open in Phoenix?? Neither side has made open looks, or much of anything.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins misses from the line, and Buie gets on the board via a high-glass layup. 8-4 Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A bad pass from Langborg allows Frankie Collins to lay it in, plus the foul.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern's defense has been terrific so far, forcing two steals and holding ASU to 1-for-6 from the field.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins and Langborg trade open threes, and that takes us to the under-16. It's 6-2 Northwestern.

The two teams are shooting 3-for-12 so far.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry's fading jumper is cash after the Nicholson miss, so NU leads by four.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson misses both, and I am yet again asking how Northwestern is this bad at making free throws.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry hits one free throw, and Nicholson draws contact after a good feed by Langborg. Still 4-2 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jamiya Neal converts a layup for ASU, but Barnhizer hits a corner three to get the 'Cats on the board. 3-2 NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The two teams are a combined 0-for-6 so far in the first 90 seconds.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson wins the tip, and we're off.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern trotting out its usual starting five in Phoenix with Boo Buie, Ty Berry, Ryan Langborg, Brooks Barnhizer and Matthew Nicholson.

The Sun Devils will start former Illini Adam Miller for the second straight game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The ‘Cats will look for a critical non-con win on national TV.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up Braun's presser. We'll hear from him next on Friday from Vegas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said NU will no longer have a director of player personnel.

In terms of desirable traits, he wants "what it understands to scout and evaluate and project a young man — not who he is, but who he can be. I'm looking for guys that have some experience at lower levels."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Was also grateful for the efforts of Johnny Kovach, Bryan Payton and Lauren McCree.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on filling recruiting staff openings: "We have this opportunity to really zoom out. How is the landscape really operating in college football?"

Said there will be "restructuring."

"We're gonna rethink it a little bit."

Also praised the departing Todd McShane.

Name: Inside NU
Content: More: "We're not concerned with what other people think. We fully trust our process."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on this class: "I think it totally aligns with [being a developmental program]."

Talked about evaluating DL Callen Campbell and navigating through snow, plus S Tito Williams and TE Patrick Schaller.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on potential players who could see the field early: "Dashun Reeder's just a really dynamic player. It'll be interesting to see how quickly he'll pick things up."

Added that his hit "percentage" on that is "not very good."  He didn't expect Michael Kilbane not to redshirt.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun also noted that he wants to do "everything in [his] power" to support Schmidt.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Jacob Schmidt and TrueNU in recruiting: "NIL and the football program have to be completely separate. We're going to be compliant in the way we operate..."

Said that he was out in New York to "build relationships" with alumni to "tell the story of our guys."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Ryan Boe: "It's a really unique situation. As we went through this process of filling out the '24 class with the QB, my initial thoughts were, 'If we're going to take somebody late like this, it's got to be the right person.'"

Mentioned Skip Holtz' evaluation of QBs.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun specified a safety that can play nickel without Rod Heard II.

"From there, we'll continue to take it one day at a time."

Noted that the player "needs to be our kind of guy" and "team-first."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on what NU is looking for in the portal: "The overall numbers is certainly a crunch right now. It's a good problem to have; it means that we have a bunch of guys that want to stay."

Noted decisions that will be made in the next two weeks.

Mentioned OL and DB as areas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said that, if Timi Oke were living in the Chicago area, he "might have an offer from every program in the country."

"He loves football. He wants to be pushed."

Noted that he probably won't be ready to go right away, but that the team is "playing the long game."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
"I would've felt that way five years ago. But to be honest, in the new age of recruiting, and the new landscape of college football, I care less about those rankings."

Stressed finding "tough, resilient, team-first" guys who "value a Northwestern degree."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on whether the staff cares about the class's ranking, and his messages to fans: "If you're looking for a guy in this position that cares about those rankings, I'm the wrong guy."

Mentions Carmine Bastone and P.J. Spencer as examples of walk-on players who weren't touted.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "No final decisions have been made."

Noted that Kurt Anderson has been "heavily involved" in OL recruiting.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said there is "need" to have more O-line signees in the second signing period, plus in the portal.

"Not to take anyone's job; to simply bolster the depth in that room. Let that room go compete."

Said the OL needs to be "revered as one of the best in the Big Ten."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said "a lot of things" determined Josh Priebe's transfer, and called him an "incredible young man."

Noted that his statement "did lead to further conversations" with OL recruits.

"I welcome that. Excited for us to continue to prep for Las Vegas."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on talking to recruits amid uncertainty: "One-on-one, private conversations, I'll keep those private. The way that I've moved and operated through all of this post-Illinois is with honesty and transparency."

Called it the "only proper way to move forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on roster size: "With our retention, we're essentially at our limit for scholarship. We're going to have to do a lot of work with getting some guys to walk-on. We have a roster limit of 112 right now.

Said there are a "couple positions" that NU will monitor in the portal.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "I can tell you firsthand: this morning was an exciting time."

Posited celebrating the finalization of the class, and bowl game prep.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun called it "critical" to have players that "value a Northwestern degree" and which want to be part of a team.

Noted that college football is becoming "more transactional and more transient," and that NU wants guys who are "invested in one another."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "Excited about this class for a lot of reasons. The athletic traits that we're looking for are critical pieces to winning in the Big Ten. We were really intentional with this class."

Stressed a love for football and wanting to be pushed, plus intelligence.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun's opening statement: "Exciting day for Northwestern football."

Said the staff was up at 3:30 a.m. PT this morning.

On the class: "It spans a lot of different areas of the country." Noted midwest roots.

"It was a unique recruiting cycle."

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun set to speak to the media shortly about National Signing Day and the Wildcats' Class of 2024. Stay tuned for updates!

Name: Inside NU
Content: A win against Utah could turn the page for Northwestern, as eyes begin to shift ahead toward the realignment era of college football:

Content: Bump bump bump

Content: In a year full of turbulence, Northwestern’s trip to Vegas should serve as an exclamation on a surprisingly successful season and a beacon of hope for the future:

Content: All season, Northwestern has struggled on the glass. Those issues, its small size and its slow pace of play create a unique statistical profile that might be a cause for concern entering January:

Name: Inside NU
Content: It was an up-and-down Week 15 for ‘Cats in the pros, but it was a busy one:

Content: Stay up to date with Northwestern wrestling before conference matchups in the new year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Just because Geno Smith is active does not mean he’s starting. The Seahawks are dressing three QBs tonight but have not announced a starter. twitter.com/AdamSchefter/s…

Name: Inside NU
Content: Which players are in/out for Utah? What does Kyle Whittingham’s team excel in? Get familiar with the Utes as  takes a deep dive into Northwestern’s bowl game opponent.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
It was not a pretty week for the ‘Cats. 

NU showed its vulnerabilities for teams to exploit for the rest of the season.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern gets a much-needed win with a 20-point victory over Bradley.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With a 86-66 win over Bradley, Northwestern snaps its six-game losing streak.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats hold on to a double-digit lead with under four minutes left in the game, 77-65.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats were a different team out of the half, ousting the Braves 27-15 in the third quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats take a 65-54 lead into the final frame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: An 11-point run puts the 'Cats ahead 53-42.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Melannie Daley puts NU back ahead. Daley has 11 points, 3 rebounds and 4 steals.

Name: Inside NU
Content: At the end of the half, Northwestern trails by just one, 39-38.

Name: Inside NU
Content: In 12 minutes, Bradley has committed six turnovers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: All tied up again with three minutes left in the first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A seven-point run has put Bradley up 34-31, Northwestern has not scored in over three minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After two free throws, Walsh is up to ten points. The first player of either team to cross into double digits.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Caleigh Walsh and Maggie Pina score the first two baskets of the second quarter to bring the 'Cats within one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats trail 24-19 at the end of the first quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern finally responds to Bradley's nine-point run on a layup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bradley is up to a 20-14 lead. Northwestern is struggling to halt Reagan Barkema who already has nine points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two threes from Caroline Lau puts the 'Cats up 12-10 within five minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NU women's basketball looks to snap its losing streak against Bradley today at home. Follow along for updates.

Name: Inside NU
Content: For the final time in 2023, we’d like to invite everyone to participate in our HOLIDAY MAILBAGWhether it is Northwestern sports-related or not, we want to hear from you!! We’ll answer as many as we can in a mailbag that will go up before Saturday’s Las Vegas Bowl.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A rock fight at its finest.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 56, Depaul 46

It wasn't pretty, but the 'Cats get back in the win column. Nick Martinelli led the 'Cats with 16 points, and Ryan Langborg added 14 points.

It is the first road win by a ranked 'Cats squad since 1969.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Langborg gets his hand on a Blue Demon's pass, but the 'Cats cannot score.

Doesn't matter though, this one is over.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Nicholson smokes two layups, but the 'Cats retain possession.

The 'Cats need more from their big man, badly.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Flagrent 1 assessed on the Blue Demons, so Buie knocks down a pair of free throws.

56-43 NU with 2 minutes to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Ryan Langborg is doing everything.

He just hit a spinning, fade-away bucket and then dove on the loose ball to give the 'Cats possession.

Gotta think Chris Collins is happy he got the Princeton transfer.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Langborg picks up his third foul, and Depaul will get two more shots.

Depaul has not made a field goal in nearly 10 minutes, but is still hanging around.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Martinelli with a sweet hook shot in the paint.

He has 16.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Another possession where Buie loses his dribble, and Langborg ends up fouling on the loose ball.

With Depaul in the bonus, 'Cats gifting the Blue Demons points.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Barnhizer breaks NU's three-minute scoring drought with a three.

50-38 NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
'Cats cannot control the basketball, dribbling it all over the place.

The mistakes are starting to add up.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Ty Berry's three hits off the front rim.

Just not his night.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie's heat check is no good, but Depaul takes an even worse shot.

Timeout Wildcats with 8:30 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Martinelli grabs an offensive board and spins his way for two.

'Cats now lead by double-digits.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson picks up his forth foul with still 10 minutes to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After forcing a shot clock expiration, Boo Buie hits a stepback three to make it a nine-point lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content:

Content: Northwestern has now lost one of the more shocking games of the 2023-24 college basketball season.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Chicago State 75, No. 25 Northwestern 73

Wesley Cardet Jr. was way too much for the Wildcats to handle, accruing 30 points. Boo Buie had 23, and Ryan Langborg posted 18, but it still wasn't enough.

That ranking will be no more.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Successful inbound by Chicago State, and that's it.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie hits a quick runner, but there's less than a second left, and Northwestern is still losing by two.

The 'Cats will need a true miracle.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer's pass is knocked away by Cardet, and there are only five seconds left. Still NU ball.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Neal makes the second. Northwestern trails by four with 6.4 left.

Yes, you need a three here.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Neal misses the first. Still life.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chicago State successfully inbounds, and Berry commits a foul with 6.4 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie makes both free throws. 74-71 Cougars, and Collins calls TO with 7.3 left. Need a steal here, realistically.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Crawford makes two free throws, and the Cougars foul up by five with 7.3 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry misses an open three, and Northwestern is still down three with 9.7 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Neal makes both. 72-69 Chicago State with 16.3 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats couldn't successfully foul on their first try, and A.J. Neal will finally head to the line with 16.3 left. One-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After review, Barnhizer did indeed touch it last. Chicago State ball.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie's floater is no good, and Chicago State recovers it. Play is under review.

19.7 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chicago State's bucket is taken away after the ruling that Cardet was out. 'Cats can take the lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie hits both. It's 70-69 Chicago State.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie slips but is awarded a foul. He'll head to the line with the Wildcats losing by three, and only 64 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie misses a layup, and Cardet splashes a three over Nicholson. Wow.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Cardet weaves his way in and now has 27 (!) points. All knotted up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern’s sixth-straight loss was the result of a familiar problem: a very slow start.

Name: Inside NU
Content:

Terrific play by Barnhizer on the other end to set it up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Who else but Buie to tie things up with a quick cut and layup. Three minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Berry stepped out of bounds on the inbound, and the Cougars have it.

14th turnover of the night for NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Buie misses a floater, but the 'Cats will keep it after the under-4. Cougars lead the Wildcats 65-63.

Just 3:53 separates Northwestern from what would be an incomprehensible loss.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Nicholson misses the free throw. Still a two-point hole with 4:13 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Northwestern beats the press and finds Nicholson, who rolls to the rim and finishes through the whistle. The big man has a chance to cut the lead to one.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
WBB: FINAL: DePaul 90, Northwestern 65

An encouraging second half from the 'Cats, who actually outscored DePaul over the final two frames, but a slow start proved to be way too much to overcome.

It's shaping up to be an all-time night of Northwestern basketball.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Corbett makes one. It's now 65-61 Chicago State.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Berry has it stripped away, and Buie fouls Corbett.

Name: Inside NU

Name: Inside NU
Content:

The Cougars are enjoying an 8-0 run at the perfect time.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Northwestern turns it over on the inbound, and the Cougars have retaken the lead on a Cardet slam. Unbelievable.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: After two NU misses, Cardet hits a three of his own. The Northwestern advantage is only one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Brent Davis drills a difficult three, and the Cougars have life. It's back to a four-point lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Langborg is fouled and makes one. It's 61-54 'Cats with 7:35 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: With under five minutes to play, DePaul still leads by 29 points despite a solid second-half offensive output from the 'Cats. It should be all but over.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Cardet makes a layup. He's up to 20 points, and that takes us to the under-8. Northwestern clinging to a 60-54 lead.

The 'Cats have made six of their last 10 shots, which has sparked a major turnaround in this second half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Martinelli gets on the board with two from the line, and the NU lead has increased to eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Chicago State has made one of its last eight field goals, and Jernigan has fouled out. A critical loss for a Cougars lineup that's already small.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Barnhizer is starting to find it. The junior works down low and gets the hook shot to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Cardet finishes through contact over Barnhizer after a change from a charge to a block. He makes the free throw, and it's back to a four-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Barnhizer again splits, and it's 56-49 Northwestern with 10:35 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Out of the media timeout, Barnhizer hits one free throw, but immediately draws another two after a strong offensive rebound.

Name: Inside NU
Content:

Chicago State hasn't made a bucket in almost six minutes of game action, which has fueled a 54-49 NU lead.

Ryan Langborg has 17, while Boo Buie has tacked on 13.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: After a made free throw from CSU, Buie gets an impressive teardrop to fall. Still a five-point lead for the 'Cats with 11:25 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
WBB: END OF THIRD: DePaul 72, Northwestern 47

The 'Cats outscore the Blue Demons, and excel on the offensive end, shooting 59% on the quarter. Caroline Lau and Casey Harter shined in particular, combining for 18 of NU's 28 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: The bottom of the net has No. 5's number handy. He hits his FIFTH triple, and the 'Cats have a five-point lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Berry banks in a ridiculous, last-second three to give the Wildcats back the lead! Unreal way for him to get on the scoreboard.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: The 'Cats really showing signs of life now, and Lau is excelling on both on ends. A nice block on a layup for her. NU is 6 of its last 7 from the field.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Langborg converts a J after a nice steal by Martinelli, and Chicago State has called timeout.

First real surge in momentum for the 'Cats since the early portions of the evening.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Barnhizer weaves his way in, draws contact and goes 1-for-2 from the stripe. Now a three-point matchup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Corbett sinks two from the line. Chicago State has doubled its advantage and is leading by four with 14:56 remaining.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Langborg hits his fourth three of the game after the timeout. Lead is cut to two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A 7-0 run for the 'Cats, as Lau has caught fire with another three and a layup. DePaul takes a timeout with 3:35 left in the third, with its lead standing at 63-39.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: At the under-16, it's Chicago State 45, Northwestern 40.

The Wildcats are 1-for-5 in the second half, while CSU is 3-for-7. Collins' squad has seemed in scramble mode for much of this one, and has its back against the wall.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A three from Lau for her first points of the night, only for Sidor to bury her fifth trey. It's a 29-point ballgame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Barnhizer erases the goose egg with a spinning layup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: The Wildcats STILL haven't scored in this second half, and following two straight turnovers, the Cougars are up 45-38.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Crawford converts two free throws, and the Cougars lead by five with 17:05 to go in this ballgame.

You read that right.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A couple of buckets from Daley and Harter are answered by two three-pointers from Sidor, who now has four treys (and hasn't missed). DePaul holds its 53-27 edge as the 'Cats take a timeout.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Not even the shot clock is working right in Welsh-Ryan Arena.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A good start to the second half for the 'Cats, as Harter gets on the board with a layup. However, Mott picks up her fourth foul soon after, which should send her to the bench for at least a little while.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Buie's off on a floater, and Cameron Jernigan slams it in.

Chris Collins calls timeout with the 'Cats trailing 41-38. Northwestern hasn't scored in 2:16 of this half.

Name: Inside NU
Content:

That type of night in Evanston.

Name: Inside NU

Name: Inside NU
Content:

18 turnovers. The Blue Demons end the half on a 23-2 run. Northwestern goes the last 3:08 without scoring. Not good.

Name: Inside NU
Content:

A 10-0 run by CSU tightened things in a big way to close the first 20 minutes. What also didn't help were seven turnovers by the 'Cats.

Boo Buie has 11, and Ryan Langborg has added nine. Wesley Cardet Jr. has been impressive.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Two free throws from Harter break a 17-0 drought, but DePaul is scorching hot. Blue Demons are 10 of their last 11 from the field, and are up to 58% overall on the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Buie quells the visiting 10-0 run with a quick-trigger three. Lead back to NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Noble Crawford knocks away a lax pass from Nick Martinelli, and goes coast to coast. The Cougars now lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: It is *another* 15-0 run for DePaul after a Shakara McCline triple. Blue Demons lead 39-17.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Corbett has scored CSU's last eight points, and all of a sudden, it's tied at 33-33.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: At the under-4, Northwestern is holding on to a narrow 33-31 lead over Chicago State.

This one is starting to take the shape of previous non-con games earlier this year, where the Wildcats haven't fully seized control.

Additionally, Ty Berry is scoreless so far.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Corbett hits again, and it's suddenly a two-point affair. The Cougars are 5-for-14 from three.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Jahsean Corbett drills a far three, and the Cougars are down just five.

Name: Inside NU

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Berry throws a beautiful lob to Nicholson, who flushes it. 31-25 'Cats with 5:24 to go in the first half.

Name: Inside NU

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Cardet nails a jumper, and the Cougars only are down six. Chicago State is hanging around so far.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: CASEY HARTER AND-ONE! Back to single digits. She made some big second-quarter plays on Sunday to bring NU back from an early deficit at Maryland, and the 'Cats will need her again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Three straight offensive rebounds from DePaul to open the second quarter, and it culminates in a Gilbert bucket. That encapsulates the action thus far, as it's 22-10 DePaul.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Nicholson lays one in and adds the foul, so the senior will try to finish the and-one following a short pause.

Northwestern's defense has been stingy early, notching five turnovers.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
WBB: END OF FIRST: DePaul 20, Northwestern 10

A buzzer-beating Mel Daley three was a bright spot, but the Wildcats committed ten (10) turnovers in one quarter. Really tough to win that way. Daley leads NU with five points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Cardet just threw one down in ferocious fashion. My goodness.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Finally, Maggie Pina breaks the drought with a three-pointer. 18-5 Blue Demons.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: It is an 18-0 run for DePaul now after a Sidor three. For context, Northwestern's start against Omaha was historic, and that was a 17-0 run (in NU's favor).

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: At the under-12, Northwestern leads Chicago State 22-12, but the Cougars will head to the free throw line following the break.

Langborg and Buie have nine and seven, respectively. Meanwhile, Wesley Cardet Jr. has seven for CSU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: *on an offensive foul

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Langborg is now 3-for-3 from three following a great dish from Buie. NU leading by eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Lau picks up her fourth turnover of the game. There's 4:22 left in the first quarter, and DePaul leads 15-2. Northwestern hasn't scored in almost six minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Buie up to seven points, and we're not even a quarter of the way into the game. He nails a floater to make it 14-9 Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: And-one for Katlyn Gilbert. DePaul now leads 13-2 with 6:36 in the first quarter, is on a 13-0 run, and is 5-of-6 from the field. Not great!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Another bucket for Peoples, who has five points and a 10-2 lead. Northwestern has struggled mightily with starting fast, and this is Exhibit A. Three turnovers for the 'Cats already.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Buie gets a trey of his own, and that takes us into the under-16 with the Wildcats leading 10-7.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: DePaul picks up eight points in a hurry, and Anaya Peoples is everywhere. 8-2 Blue Demons.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: A three from Ryan Langborg ties things up 7-7. Two turnovers already for the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
WBB: FINAL: Maryland 71, Northwestern 58  
A pair of threes from Alana Goodchild make this a little closer than it appeared. NU flashed resilience in the second quarter, but ultimately, turnovers and shooting slumps allowed UMD to pull away and hand NU its fifth-straight loss.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Rachel Mutombo getting her first minutes in purple and white!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: RYAN LANGBORG IS SCORCHING HOT!!

He hits his fourth three of the half to give him 16. 

40-28 NU

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Langborg put the ‘Cats on his back, splashing his third three of the game to end a near 4 minute field goal drought, giving NU a 37-26 lead with 3:30 left in the half

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A crafty layup from Lau cuts the deficit to 15, but Kubek responds with a trey. Maryland back up by 18 with just over five minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: The Maryland lead has grown to 20, and it's all but over with seven minutes left barring a miracle.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: A Martinelli triple give NU a 32-19 lead at the under 8 timeout. 

The sophomore already has 9

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Barnhizer finds the net for the first time in the game, drilling a wide-open three.

Langborg hits another triple to make it 27-17.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Detroit Mercy hits a three, but Martinelli hits his signature floater to respond.

However, both teams missed the rim badly on their next possession.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
WBB: END OF THIRD: Maryland 56, Northwestern 39

The Wildcats were outscored 20-6 in the period. They shot 3-of-16 from the field in the quarter. Just unable to string together consistency.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Technical Foul on Detroit Mercy gifts Northwestern two free throws, but Buie splits the pair.

With the extra possession, Martinelli lays it in to make it 19-12 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MBB: Hunger makes a pair of free throws to make it 16-10 Northwestern.

Buie and Barnhizer still scoreless nearly halfway through the first frame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Two jumpers from Daley are true to sandwich a Maryland transition bucket. 50-39 Terps, with two minutes left in the third quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Shyanne Sellers has five steals. Northwestern has 17 turnovers, and the third quarter isn't over yet. Not great!

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: With more than 15 minutes left in the game, Mott picks up her fourth foul on an illegal screen.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Just like that, another Sellers bucket gives UMD a double-digit lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: It's been all Berry and Langborg, each with five early as NU holds a 12-8 lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: A three from Alexander and a couple of rough possessions on offense from the 'Cats extend Maryland's lead to 40-33 with 7:35 in the third period.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Still 7-5 NU at the first media timeout.

Name: Inside NU
Content: No foul. Kubek checks out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Mid range jumper from Berry breaks the tie at 7-5

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Allie Kubek was down after getting hit in the face. Officials appear to be reviewing it.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Langborg buries a three on NU's first possession

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Nicholson wins the tip and we are underway.

Name: Inside NU
Content: WBB: Second half has begun from College Park. Northwestern is in great position to force this one to come down to the wire if it can keep its second-quarter performance up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MBB: Same starters as usual for NU with Buie-Berry-Langborg-Barnhizer-Nicholson on the floor.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern takes the floor for the first time in over a week, and we have everything you need to know before tipoff.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALFTIME: Maryland 36, Northwestern 33

After a slow start offensively, Northwestern got hot. The defense also shined. Weaver has 9 points, with Walsh and Daley contributing 6 points apiece.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Casey Harter tying the game with a trey AGAIN! But Sellers answers with one of her own to beat the halftime buzzer.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver's free throw is good. The 'Cats are leading on the road.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hailey Weaver with an and-one in transition! She's got eight points, and Northwestern has a chance to take the lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paige Mott picks up her third foul, and UMD ends a scoring drought that lasted nearly three minutes with a score from Sellers. Really, really encouraging stretch from NU's defense, though.

Name: Inside NU
Content: CASEY HARTER STEPBACK THREE! It's tied at 27 in College Park!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Walsh with another bucket, and Lau already has five assists. She's shined as a playmaker thus far. Maryland leads 27-22 with 4:40 in the half to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's the same picture.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's three steals for UMD's Shyanne Sellers, but Harter draws a charge in transition. 22-16 Maryland with 7:47 left in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mel Daley makes another midrange jumper. Surely, that sentence has never been repeated before.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern opens the second quarter with a starting five of Pina-Harter-Daley-McWilliams-Ademusayo. The Terps, in contrast, are playing most of their starters with an eight-point lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF FIRST: Maryland 22, Northwestern 14

NU is shooting just 31% from the field, and a couple of runs from the Terps have opened it up. Weaver and Kubek lead all scorers with 6 points through 10 minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Maryland really starting to get out in transition. The Terps have already forced Daley to turn it over three times in four minutes of play. It'll end the quarter strong with a swift run.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A nice rejection by Caroline Lau, but UMD ends up scoring on the same possession. It's another 6-0 run for Maryland, which leads 16-10.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mel Daley (who's coming off the bench today) trades buckets with Alexander. Still a two-point game in Maryland's favor with under three minutes to play in the first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And on cue, Walsh scores, followed by a Weaver jumper. No. 11 has 6 points already, and it's a 10-8 ballgame.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
A couple UMD buckets answer some Weaver free throws, and it's -10-4 Maryland.

Caileigh Walsh is 0-of-4 from the field, and NU hasn't scored in over four minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A UMD bucket gives the Terps the lead, but both teams are shooting a combined 3-of-13 from the field thus far.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver and Allie Kubek trade layups, and we're even at two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Tip is up, and we're underway.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern's starters: 

Caroline Lau
Hailey Weaver
Casey Harter
Caileigh Walsh
Paige Mott

Walsh is back in the starting lineup, and Harter is going to get the first start of her career in purple and white.

Name: Inside NU
Content: tips off its conference slate in College Park in just under 10 minutes! Follow along here for tweets/updates!

Name: Inside NU
Content: “It’s hard to contend that Northwestern shouldn’t already be looking to its 2024 roster via the portal’s first window — attracting impact players as early as possible while still maintaining its priorities of fit and character,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: In two weeks, Northwestern will take the turf at Allegiant Stadium to play Utah in the Las Vegas Bowl. Before then, get up to speed with the program’s bowl history, for all of its ups and downs.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Shohei Ohtani is actually a Northwestern Wildcat

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Priebe is the fourth ‘Cat to enter the transfer portal. Yet, leaves a return open if Kurt Anderson is retained. 

While injuries derailed his last two seasons, Priebe played nearly every snap this season, finishing with a 61.2 blocking grade from PFF. 

Best of luck to No. 68!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Another upset means another long basketball pod episode, which means Episode 2 of Rock Fight:

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's OK the Cubs can keep Cody Bellinger now

Name: Inside NU
Content: The three EICs of this site would like you to know that the Yankees are indeed back

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams is the third Wildcat to enter the transfer portal. The DB played 175 special teams snaps over the last three years, but only saw time in Weeks 1-4 this year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: “Pick your poison for which upset was bigger, but these two wins are just the beginning of the story Northwestern basketball is writing,” writes @ACBSports18.

Name: Inside NU
Content: One thing’s for sure...Northwestern will have its hands full with an impressive Utah team:

Name: Inside NU
Content: The weekly NFL check-in features a new face and some strong performances.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Eight Wildcats joined Katie Ledecky at the 2023 U.S. Open Championships last week.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Freeman is now the second Wildcat to enter the portal. He played in three games for the 'Cats last year, and has consistently drawn praise for his scout team work.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern moves up to 29th in the newest AP Poll. Big Ten teams ahead include Purdue (No. 4), Illinois (No. 20, Wisconsin (23) and Ohio State (27).

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown mentions not wanting to overload players between now and the Maryland game next Sunday due to Finals Week.

Notes that the quarter system makes it difficult because the only period in which the players don't have class is between next weekend and before Christmas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on why the 'Cats seem to start slow: 

"We seem to be waiting around defensively...we got to rebound the ball, that'll let us get out and run a little more."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Freeman is now the second Wildcat to enter the portal. He played in three games for the 'Cats last year, and has consistently drawn praise for his scout team work.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on utilizing a deep bench (had 10 different scorers today):

"Didn't help us today...It certainly is going to help us down the road."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on starting Alana Goodchild over Caileigh Walsh: 

"She has a scorer's mentality, and we've been struggling to score the ball."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown in his opening statement: "We got to find players that want to rebound the basketball."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown mentions having opportunities to fight back in the third quarter, but not converting on chances.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Joe McKeown now stepping up to the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McWilliams on being out-rebounded: "It's about toughness. We're being soft in there."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McWilliams on starting slow: "We just got to come out and be ready to play."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Pina on getting open looks from three: "[My teammates] were just able to find me a lot easier this game."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jasmine McWilliams and Maggie Pina head to the podium to kick off the presser.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A four game losing streak heading into Big Ten play is...not ideal.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Georgetown 82, Northwestern 58. 

It was all Hoyas this afternoon, as they managed to out-rebound NU, 35-25, and got to the line 12 more times.

The 'Cats drop to 3-5 on the season. They'll kick off conference play against Maryland a week from today.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
With 1:35 left to go and Georgetown up by 22, the Hoyas put in their substitutes. 

This one looks about over.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Caileigh Walsh is making it happen for the 'Cats.

She fought for a jump ball on defense and turned the following possession into two made layups at the free throw line. She has 13 on the day.

77-55, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
One step forward, two steps back.

Coming out of the timeout, Georgetown scores a bucket under the basket, Lau turns it over, and the Hoyas drain a floater.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
CASEY HARTER NAILS A THREE ASSISTED BY LAU.

'Cats have cut the lead to 15, and there's 6:57 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Through 1:30 of this quarter, defense has been stifling on both ends.

68-50, Hoyas ahead.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The third quarter comes to a close, and the 'Cats find themselves down 20.

Lau, Walsh and Weaver continue to put together solid offensive outings, but turnovers and a lack of rebounds has put NU in a tough hole to climb out of.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern has started to play a very aggressive press, and it seems to be working.

Georgetown has turned it over a few times now from the double- and triple-teams.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lau drains a three to cut the deficit to 19.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Coming out of the timeout, Joe McKeown subs the whole lineup.

Most of the starters are coming in with 3:31 left in Q3.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Maggie Pina connects on a *difficult* three.

Looks like she might've even drawn a foul on it, but nothing gets called.

62-38, 'Cats trail.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
NU pushes it in transition as Ademusayo finishes with a nice layup.

Georgetown comes down the court with an answer of its own.

57-35, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver scores a TOUGH floater. 

She's looked excellent today.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
During the timeout, they just had a fan play a game based on whether or not Paige Mott could name more than six sports in 15 seconds...

Hammering the over.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mercy Ademusayo gets her first points of the day on a layup that was nicely assisted by McWilliams.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver gets big to score the 'Cats' first points of the period, driving down the lane through a few defenders.

53-29, Georgetown.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Third quarter is underway, and it starts with a Hailey Weaver three rimming out.

Georgetown takes it down the court and scores on a jumper.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern had five defensive rebounds in the first half. Georgetown had 12 offensive boards.

That'll need to change in these last two quarters to keep NU in this.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up Braun's presser.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun said he was in his office when he heard that NU was headed to Vegas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
More: "I think it's really important that we take that opportunity to reflect on what this group has achieved and the story has written together.

"It's really special. Today is one of those days we have to take a step back and recognize the opportunity this is for the program."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on what today was like: "I don't know if I've had a chance to really take that deep breath and enjoy it. I look forward to that post-bowl game with [my] family."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun noted A.J. Henning, Ben Bryant, Richie Hagarty, Cam Johnson as examples of not necessarily being the highest-ranked transfers, but ones that fit well with Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: He added: "It's being intentional about the things that matter right now, and that starts with doing a great job with connecting with our current roster while also identifying our needs."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the impact of the portal and staff additions looming on bowl prep: "It's fluid. It's not easy, there's a lot going on. Referencing back to the staffing of this program, the staffing within our recruiting and staffing will look different from the amount of people."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun:  "I see [the bowl game] as an opportunity to put an exclamation point on this season."

Name: Inside NU
Content: He mentioned his NDSU experience, and prepping for playoff games with a national title on the line.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the difference in between a bowl and true road game: "It's tremendously different. 

"We're going to ensure that everyone in the program has an opportunity to enjoy this experience. And to be honest, that's a little different from what I'm accustomed to."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Fitting for the way this game has gone so far, Georgetown benefits from a bad NU possession and nails a three-pointer to close the half.

It's been all Hoyas through 20 minutes. They lead 51-27.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on recruiting and making additions: "I'm really excited about the opportunity we have to move forward. There's balance in all that."

Shouted out multiple members of the program in the building (Bryan Payton, Lauren McCree, etc.) on the recruiting side.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Walsh's three rims out, and Harter nabs the rebound. 

She goes up for a contested put-back but doesn't get the call.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun continues to praise Utah: "Haven't had much of an opportunity to watch much of them. But the one thing I can say is, you know you're going to get a team that plays complementary football, a team that plays physical football."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Walsh heads to the line and hits both. 

48-27, Georgetown leads.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on seeing Whittingham in the 2009 Sugar Bowl: "I remember that game vividly. I remember as a young coach, walking the halls at a GAs coaching convention, and being like, 'Hey, that's Coach Whittingham.'"

Praised Utah's developmental system.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
GTown is playing with pace, and it looks to be tiring the ‘Cats out. 

Trips to the free throw line have become commonplace in this second period. 

46-25, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said he doesn't anticipate any Northwestern player opting out for the Vegas Bowl.

Emphasized transparency and communication in those conversations.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver draws a foul on a shot in the paint. 

She sinks one at the line, narrowing the lead to 17.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Said the team had the day off today with finals coming up and staff members on the road for recruiting.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on talking to the other coaches and players about going to Vegas: "The only thing I've seen is some of these group chats absolutely buzzing when the news came out."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Kelsey Ransom has scored 15 for Georgetown in the first 17 minutes of play. A major problem for this ‘Cats defense. 

42-24, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on using the bowl game prep as a developmental opportunity for the entire roster: "It's unique. December 23rd is an awfully early bowl game. Great benefit as well. We're two practices in, which were utilized for development of our entire roster."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Noted their Pac-12 title game win last season as a model of "winning football."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Scoring is ramping up now, as the teams are trading shots. 

The difference maker is second-chance points. On nearly every possession, Georgetown is getting an ORB or trip to the free throw line. 

38-22, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on facing Kyle Whittingham: "It'll be a tremendous challenge. I don't think Coach Whittingham knows this, but I'll commonly use the Utah program model as one I admire."

Said he did professional development at Utah, and developed respect for the way the program was built.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun doesn't anticipate staff changes before the bowl game.

"No decisions have been made on staffing. We started this thing off together, and we fully anticipate on December 23rd we'll have this group together."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mott gets charged with her third foul and heads to the bench.

Georgetown converts an and-one. 

34-18, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "This group certainly is thrilled, and knows there's a lot of work ahead to be ready and at our best on the 23rd."

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun's bowl game presser starting now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern is pressing now.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HUSTLE. 

Lau takes a few threes, misses both, Weaver collects the ORBs before Pina coverts on a deep shot. 

31-18, GTown.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mott opens scoring for NU in the second quarter. Georgetown answers right back. 

31-15, Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The Hoyas nail their fifth three of the day. 

27-13, Northwestern trails.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The second quarter opens with a foul on the ‘Cats. 

Georgetown sinks both free throws, extending its lead to 11.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The first quarter ends as NU seems to be finding a footing on offense. 

22-13, Georgetown leads.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Caileigh Walsh makes her first shot of the day — a nice jumper. 

22-13, ‘GTown.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
After cashing in on two three-pointers, Lau has missed two tough contested layups. 

22-11, ‘Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HEAT CHECK. 

LAU SPLASHES A DEEP THREE WITH A HAND IN HER FACE. 

18-11, ‘Hoyas.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lau responds with Northwestern’s first three of the day. 

18-8, GTown.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paige Mott gets called for a foul, and with the Hoyas already in the bonus, they’ll go to the line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With 3:42 left in Q1, Georgetown leads Northwestern, 17-4.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Officially, it’ll be the Wildcats and the Utes squaring off on Dec. 23 from Vegas.

Name: Inside NU
Content: BREAKING: Northwestern is Vegas-bound! It’s a rematch of the 2018 Holiday Bowl out west with the Utes.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
“Northwestern is an under-recruited point guard like Buie. It was too small. It wasn’t supposed to win getting outrebounded 52-27. Every success story should be the exception… 

“They remembered the feeling, and wrote this story,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lucas Oil Stadium has played host to some pretty great college football games. 

Ahead of Michigan-Iowa,  ranked all nine Big Ten Championships from the CFP era.

Name: Inside NU
Content: So that really happened.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The officials beat Purdue

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue having the court/field stormed three times against Northwestern in 2023

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue blowing another lead at Welsh-Ryan Arena

Name: Inside NU
Content: Presser is done. And let the memes begin.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie: " is unbelievable, so be able to get that win tonight... it's good that they got to go out and do what they came out for."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Berry on Hunger, Preston, Nicholson: "The big men, they played great. Edey's so hard to guard, and I can only imagine how hard they had to fight."

Said that rotating the bigs seemed to help wear Edey down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry on NU's ball security: "We pride ourselves on taking care of the ball. If you can take care of the ball and stay in the single digits, you can give yourselves a chance."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on creating late in the clock: "I just try to make the right read every time. We have great players around me, so I'm going to pass if two guys are on the ball. That's the way you've got to play basketball. It just creates havoc for the defense."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry: "The crowd was amazing tonight. You're tired, but then you just hear the crowd erupt. It makes you want to play even more, even when you don't have anything left in the tank."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry on the message in the huddle after Edey's shot at the end of regulation: "We knew it wasn't going to be easy. We came together in that huddle and said, we were gonna get it done the hard way regardless."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry on stepping up: "It's awesome, but also relying on my teammates to get me the ball and get big shots like that."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry on himself, Buie and Langborg: "Me and Ryan, we play our part. Just being ready when Boo hits us to knock down shots."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on the offensive success: "I think we just did a really good job of just moving the ball offensively."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins to the student-journalists (yours truly): "Good luck with finals. Do your own work."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry up next.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins said that hard-hedging was an adjustment after Smith successfully got downhill early on.

"We were trying to do it to start the game, and then we did it more to take him out of his rhythm."

Said NU did a good job of tagging Edey on ball screen actions late.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On his message to the bigs: "Every foul against Edey has to matter."

Said to Preston, Hunger and Nicholson that they all had to be ready to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Edey: "I think if you take Boo off the floor, it's a similar impact to taking Edey off the floor for Purdue."

Compared Edey's impact and dominance to Tim Duncan andTyler Hansbrough, who he coached or played against.

"For him to play 38 minutes is impressive."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "When I came 11 years ago, I didn't come to go to a tournament one time. I came to build a program where year in and year out we could be competitive." -Collins

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on the current status of the program: "Let's get to a point where games like this, they're great to win them, but have them be a part of who we are."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on the defensive success: "We just try to swarm, try to have active hands. Try to double Edey every time he touches it."

Credited Painter for making their rotations difficult, and for helping Purdue create some open threes.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Langborg: "We just knew he was a fit. We were out in Sacramento together with him.

Said if Audige and Buie were back, they knew they wanted Langborg.

"He's better of the bounce than people give him credit for."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on Luke Hunger: "I love Luke. For all intents and purposes, he's a freshman. He's been waiting for his opportunity, and these last couple of games, I'm seeing equity with his teammates, with the coaches. To battle with Zach is a testament to his confidence."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins said it was "huge" to reduce Purdue's lead to eight entering the break.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on his message after going down 13: "Just that it was a long game. We felt like that we were making some errors on the defensive side of the floor. Our ball screen defense wasn't great tonight. I thought our post stuff was pretty good, actually."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Buie's performance: "He thrives in these types of games.  I would not trade him for anybody. I'm glad he's on my team."

Says he didn't call a timeout at the end of regulation cause all he would have done was draw a play up for No.0

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on Buie saying this was a battle between the two best post players in the country (himself and Edey): "Humble!"

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins: "We've got to keep growing. It's still Dec. 1. It's sure a heck of a lot better winning it [tonight]."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on the backcourt: "I thought we did some really good things. Even in the first half, I thought we were getting what we wanted.

"You've got to play in the midrange against this team. They make you do that."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "I think that we made a statement as a school."

Said that, in addition to academics, "we can have some fun."

"This atmosphere was as good as anything I've been in."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins credited Berry for closing the game out.

"We knew what they were going to do [at the end of reuglation]. [Edey]'s just so big. They said 'Coach, we're trying, we're trying.'"

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "We battled all night. We needed coaches. We needed our scout team to get us ready."

Called Buie "sensational," especially his nine assists and zero turnovers.

"To me, as good a performance as he's had, and as any Northwestern player's had in my time here."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "Both teams kept responding. Just a big-time, high-level game. To play a league game, to take care of our home court against that team."

Said he's "not really sure" what anyone can do to defend Zach Edey because of his "size and skill level."

"We fought."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Chris Collins now at the podium.

"I'm at a little bit of a loss for words because of what a war that game was. I've been very fortunate to be a part of college basketball... That game ranks right up there in terms of the highest-level game that I've ever been a part of."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chris Collins now at the podium

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Painter on NU anticipating the hard-hedging: "Yes. They started the game in a drop a couple times."

Said Purdue got good looks, and said NU had to "sell out to Edey.

"If we played the game again I wouldn't change anything offensively, schematically."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Painter on Northwestern only committing three turnovers: "We're not a high-pressure team, but it's more a credit to them.

Said that NU's low turnover average was something that was on their radar.

"They have experience." Mentioned Barnhizer, Buie, Langborg, Berry.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Painter on NU: "This is the best game they've played all year. No question."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Painter: "When you dominate the glass like that... you expect to win."

He said the refs were "fabulous" tonight."

"But you've got to be able to stop [Northwestern], and we couldn't do that."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Painter credited Langborg. "He hadn't gotten going... he made six threes in six games, one of them was a banker. But we knew it was a matter of time before he got going."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Painter credited Boo Buie. Called him "magnificent."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Painter on differences between the post defense: "They fouled our big man 15 times. And the refs actually called it, which was pretty cool."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Painter on the turnovers: "We have to do a better job. Just feeding the post. You have to see the defense when you're passing. A couple of those, I don't think the decisions were terrible...

"What it comes down to was our inability to guard. They hit open looks, and we didn't."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Matt Painter at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hard to have stock-downs after that, but we tried...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loud chants of "Let's go" ringing from the locker room to the media room. Presser to come. It should be a legendary one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It’s a party

Name: Inside NU
Content: Zach Edey and Matt Painter sure don't want to visit Welsh-Ryan Arena again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boy, this sure feels good again.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 92, No. 1 Purdue 88

They did it again. They did it again. They did it again.

Truly one of the greatest games in the history of Northwestern Athletics. No notes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue players coming off the court now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: HISTORY REPEATS ITSELF (almost). Clock stops at 0.3 as the students briefly storm the floor. may not like that one...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry makes both. Timeout Collins. It might be happening.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Smith makes it. Two-point game. NU inbounds successfully, and Berry can all but ice it right now at the line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Smith makes the first. Let's see what happens now, with Purdue down three.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's two. That changes a lot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston fouls on a three-pointer. Smith draws it, and heads to the line for (temporarily, under review) three. It isn't over with 8.6 seconds to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie has a 30-piece. Hits both.

Name: Inside NU
Content: BLAKE PRESTON WITH THE STEAL IN THE POST AND BUIE IS HEADING TO THE LINE

Name: Inside NU
Content: He makes one of two. With 25.2 seconds left, Purdue will have a chance to tie or win.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern gets across half-court and breaks the press, and Barnhizer gets fouled. He'll have the chance to make this a three-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie misses, and Preston can't stop Edey from scoring. 87-86. Timeout on the floor, 34.1 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's a charge. Northwestern is getting the ball, and has a chance to make it a two-score game. Not sure if that's happened yet.

Name: Inside NU
Content: I have no more words for Boo Buie man. The face of Northwestern Athletics.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston forces a turnover in the post, and NU is slowing this game down now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry draws a foul after Smith turns it over. He has a chance to take the lead at the line with 2:09 to go, and does. 85-84 Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 'Cats bench urging on the crowd.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston now draws a foul from Edey (his fourth). He hits one. 84-83.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loyer draws a foul on Preston, and nails both from the line. Purdue back up by two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry now. What the hell is happening.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Big one from Loyer, who answers Buie's triple with one of his own. 82-79 PU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie man. AGAIN with the long three.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loyer splits. 79-76 now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie picks up a foul on Loyer. That's four on him.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey gets the scoring started in OT with a slam. Well over 30.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Me on the verge of having a heart attack on continuing to try and watchi this game

Name: Inside NU
Content: This is madness. Just out of a fairytale.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey scores. Overtime.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey catches it, and Purdue calls timeout. They advance the ball, and 2.7 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue has to go the length of the court. Here we go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We went down on the court and watched that as it unfolded. Holy. CrapZ

Name: Inside NU
Content: We’re on the floor. Boo Buie might have just done it again. 76-73 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie splits a pair at the line. Game tied at 74. 49 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Five fouls for Jones. The Evanston native has had a hell of a homecoming.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer with a huge steal, and Jones commits a foul on Buie as he's dribbling. Boo heads to the line for two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's hard to breathe right now. This has lived up to the hype and then some.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue keeps it. 1:03 to go, Boilers lead 74-73.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jones misses a three, and NU might get the ball back with 1:03 left. Possession under review though.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jump ball after Preston can't finish a lob. NU keeps it.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Gillis with the offensive board in traffic, and takes the lead. 1:39 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry picks up his fourth on a charge, and Purdue with a chance to take the lead here.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lance Jones, who has struggled mightily, with a tough finish over Preston. 73-72 'Cats, 2:20 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: He misses both. LOUD.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg with a huge steal, and gets fouled hard by Jones. Something something Chase Audige steal-and-slam...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg draws a foul on Smith, and drains both. 73-70 ballgame and the arena is on its feet.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston goes to the line after getting fouled by Edey. He makes one of two. 'Cats with the lead again with 3:40.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey swishes both. Even at 70.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And Nicholson picks up his fifth. Frankly, a ticky-tack call from the refs here in what's been a physical game. It should be Preston on Edey the rest of the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey splits a pair at the line after Hunger's foul. Two-point game approaching the four-minute mark.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Hunger drains a free throw at the line. 70-67 with four minutes to go, but Hunger picks up his fifth foul on Edey. He'll come out.

Really huge hand for Hunger. The best game of his career couldn't have come at a better time.

Name: Inside NU
Content: CHICKEN SANDWICH CHICKEN SANDWICH CHICKEN SANDWICHHHHHHHH

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun on the mic. If there was ever a time for complementary basketball, it's now.

Name: Inside NU
