Content: That Luke Hunger three feeling like...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loyer evens it up with a layup. Even at 66.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Luke Hunger with an and-one layup, but misses the free throw. Puts the 'Cats up two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two for him. All even at 64.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer now picks up his fourth foul defending Edey. Martinelli coming in for him, it appears.

Name: Inside NU
Content: RYAN. LANGBORG.

Name: Inside NU
Content: TKR splits. Again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hunger picks up his fourth foul, and TKR goes to the line yet again. The 'Cats just aren't fully taking advantage of the off-Edey minutes (and he's coming back on right now).

Name: Inside NU
Content: TKR goes to the line again for the Boilers, and he splits again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: You really just have to love this for Ty Berry. After some early struggles, and some heat from the fanbase, he has just been incredible. That three encapsulated it: he's been the beacon of consistency this team has needed.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kaufman-Renn splits. Two-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Langborg picks up a foul on Kaufman-Renn. 59-58 Purdue at the under-eight. 

Buckle. Your. Freaking. Seatbelts.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie draws a foul, and drains two. 21 points for him with over eight minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loud chants of "Boiler Up" again. The gym is as loud as it's been all night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Caleb Furst. Wow. He rose up and slammed it over two defenders.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey comes out of the game after a charge on Barnhizer.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ryan Langborg looking like Sacramento Langborg out here, but Edey is... Zach Edey. A slam from him gives Purdue the lead back.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson picks up his fourth with about 10 minutes to go trying to knock it away from Edey. Hunger is back in.

Name: Inside NU
Content: He splits the pair. 54-53.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer draws a foul on Furst, and heads to the line with a chance to take the lead back with 10 minutes to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern is getting outrebounded 33-17 and has this game tied. Man.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brief stoppage on here, as Caleb Furst appears to have drawn some blood.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg drains a three after missing a long two on the last possession. We're back even at 53 with 11:17 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson back in the game now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A HALF-COURT SHOT HAS BEEN HIT AT WELSH-RYAN!! A sign of things to come?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Smith gets to the basket on two straight possessions, and the Boilers have the lead back. 53-50 at the under-12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey with a dunk after Hunger doubles, but Barnhizer with a slam on the next possession. It is a ballgame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And-one. Northwestern with the lead now. 48-47.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo. Buie. END TWEET. What did we just watch??

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey snags an offensive rebound on Hunger, and heads back to the line. He splits a pair. We are four free throws from chicken...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie to Purdue’s perimeter defense

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie with another floater. He's taken over. One-point game. Foul on Hunger. 46-45, crowd is rocking at the under-16.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Call stands, and Buie hits at the line. 46-43. Huh, this is looking like a familiar story...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie with an and-one goaltend, and the 'Cats can get it to a one-score game. Play (more specifically, the goaltend) under review).

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer with a post fade after a Purdue bucket, but Buie commits a reach-in. Hunger in for Preston. 44-40 Boilers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey just baptized Preston (again)...

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg with bucket as the shot clock expired, and the Purdue lead is back down to four.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry with another one. This is great to see. The game is within four, and the crowd is LOUD.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson picks up his third foul, and immediately checks out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry drains another midrange. At last, NU is within six.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Second half underway.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALFTIME: No. 1 Purdue 40, Northwestern 32

NU just hasn't been able to get this game to six after an early shooting slump. The rotations are slightly late, which have led to some open threes. Buie leads the 'Cats with 11 points on 4/7, but Edey has 14 and has 8 FTs already.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern, in the bonus, misses at the line (Preston does).

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey picks up his second, and he comes out. Huge for the 'Cats, who really haven't been able to generate a paint attack. Loud boos from the Purdue fans.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg with a middy, followed with an over the back on Edey (his first foul). 'Cats with a chance to get it to six, which they just haven't been able to do.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston can't finish a dunk after a pass from Langborg. Golden opportunity missed for the 'Cats there.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg with a corner three, and the crowd is back in this one. A travel on Edey, and now Wildside is REALLY in this. 38-30 Boilers with 2:30 to play in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey hits a pair at the line. Seven of nine from the line already, and it's 38-27 Purdue.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Joe McKeown honored at half-court during the under-four for his Northwestern women's basketball-record 252nd win against Omaha on November 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie with the floater over Edey to respond. Just like last year, Purdue is in control early, but the 'Cats are hanging in there.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Who are you and what have you done with Blake Preston?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry is absolutely carrying this offense right now along with Buie. Smoooth Euro from him, cutting the Purdue lead to 31-23.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie with yet another bucket, and an illegal screen called on Mason Gillis.

The chants of DUI ring out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry finds Buie in the corner to keep this at 10 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry and Clayton seem to miscommunicate on defense, and it's a 13-point game after a Smith three heading into the under-eight. Chants of "Let's Go Boilers."

Name: Inside NU
Content: A money three from Berry, but the deficit stays at 10 after a layup from Furst. 26-16.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A reach-in from Clayton puts Purdue in the bonus with 8:50 to go. Not good!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry forces a turnover off the press, and Luke Hunger with some great hustle to get an offensive board, but a trey from Langborg doesn't go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie drains two at the line, and Clayton checks in for him.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey checks out for the first time, and yet the 'Cats just can't rebound. Almost three straight offensive boards for the Boilers there.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 5 of 15 from the field.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
David Braun gets a standing ovation as he lifts the HAT over his head.

"We're so excited for our bowl opportunity. It's time to take the purple to the College Football Playoff," Braun said.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson picks up his second foul on Edey, and we head into the under-12 with Purdue up 20-11.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Heide with a trey, and the Purdue lead is up to nine now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Awful possession for the 'Cats there. Martinelli holds the ball late in the shot clock, and Purdue scores on a turnover.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie with a NICE hesitation, and he glides to the rim.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braden Smith buries a triple, giving Purdue a 15-9 lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Aaaand Edey dunks on Preston's head. Might be seeing a little more of that.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nick Martinelli checks in for Berry.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 10-9 Purdue. Same thing happened here for a bit.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer with a deuce, and then Preston commits a foul on a down screen. Under-16 is here, with the 'Cats down 10-9.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loyer with the midrange J, and then Barnhizer fouls Edey. He makes both, and Blake Preston checks in for Nicholson. 10-7 Boilers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ryan Langborg from the corner for threeee!

Name: Inside NU
Content: And he responds with a post hook. 6-4 Purdue.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "F--- Zach Edey" chants already from the student section.

Name: Inside NU
Content: MATTHEW NICHOLSON OH BABY

Name: Inside NU
Content: And-one three after Berry fouls Loyer in the corner off a kick from Braden Smith. He makes the free throw, and it's 4-2.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie gets out on the fastbreak after a steal, finds Berry, and the 'Cats go up two. LOUD.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lance Jones guarding Buie.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson picks up one as Edey boxes him out. Looks like a differently reffed game than last year already.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Edey wins the tip, and we're off.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's hard not to get emotional watching this.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A LOUD "Boooo" from the crowd when Buie comes out. Absolute chills.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Purdue gets greeted with tremendous boos.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Here come the ‘Cats. 

It’s is damn loud in here

Name: Inside NU
Content: Loud cheering from the students after last year's upset is shown on the board during "Dream On."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Starters for the Boilermakers: Braden Smith, Fletcher Loyer, Lance Jones, Trey Kaufman-Renn, Zach Edey

For the Wildcats: Buie, Langborg, Berry, Barnhizer, Nicholson

Name: Inside NU
Content: T-30 minutes, and  is ROCKING.

Name: Inside NU
Content: One hour.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Everything you need to know about this Big Ten opener can be found right here:

Name: Inside NU
Content: We’re in the building. This one doesn’t need buildup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After eight years with the Wildcats, Shane Davis will no longer lead the volleyball program.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
BREAKING: Northwestern volleyball has moved on from HC Shane Davis.

The Wildcats went 15-15 and 9-11 in the Big Ten this year. They haven't finished above .500 in conference play since at least 2013.

Davis was a defendant in a hazing lawsuit, dating back to a 2021 suspension.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With the 2023 regular season having come to a close,  and  hand out some awards — including MVP, most improved and even favorite Braunism — on the 14th episode of Pound the Talk.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On a basketball (!) pod,  and  look at both Northwestern teams’ early seasons and dive into the team on everyone’s minds today:

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Happy December. Happy gameday.

Tonight, he returns.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps us up here from Welsh-Ryan.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on the differences between NU this year and last year: “We have new guys. We’re able to space the floor a little more.”

On Purdue, he’s noted that he’s depended on the scouting report.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie: “ are the best in the country. We’re going to need them tomorrow night.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on how the experience/film last year helps: “I haven’t watched too much of last year’s game, because everything is different. I’m just reading the scouting report, listening to the coaches, and trusting them.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on toughest challenge: “Zach Edey. He’s huge, and they play through him. Obviously it’s going to be a tough task with him.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on playing Purdue again after the upset: “We’re super excited. Obviously they’re the No. 1 team in the country, so that brings a lot of energy.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie up next.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry on how last season’s win affects this game: “We try not to focus on last year. It’s a new year, anyone can beat anybody.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Berry: “Every game we just pride ourselves on doing what we know. Just relying on strategies and doing what we’ve done.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on K.J. Windham: “Just a winner. Lots of toughness.

“He’s just all about winning. He fits not just as a player, but with our culture.”

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on taking steps to stay out of foul trouble: “We just have to be smarter, especially our main guys. We’re just getting too many silly ones.

Noted Buie’s foul off a turnover against NIU as an example.

“We’re going to have to have our main guys on the floor.”

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on the defense: “Work in progress. But that took time as well (last year).

Noted the Pitt, Ohio State losses as examples of growing pains. Stressed working in new pieces.

“I feel like we are getting better. I think a week of practice for us really helped.”

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on the pace: “I don’t think an up-and-down game is gonna favor us. That being said, if we force turnovers, we can push and attack.”

Said he’d prefer the game’s scoring to be in the low 60s.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on Barnhizer’s role tomorrow: “You need your guys to step up. We need Brooks to be dynamic. He’s a unique guy because he can play all over the court. We’re gonna need his production to give ourselves a chance.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins: “you’ve got to pick and choose your poison at times with this team. We’re going to have different schemes to try to get [Edey] off the block, but at the same time you’re going to give up a few shots at times.”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins noted that Braden Smith and Fletcher Loyer have taken big steps for Purdue.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins said he’d rather play Purdue later in the season because of the “better picture” from more in-season film.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: “It’s really hard to replicate Edey in practice.”

Says playing a team like Purdue, NU needs to play “a picture perfect game”

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins says tomorrow feels like a Big Game despite it being only November.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Here at Welsh-Ryan Arena for men’s basketball media availability! Chris Collins up first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern women’s basketball struggled mightily on the defensive end in Vegas and at home, which has led to a three-game losing streak:

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lawson becomes the first Northwestern player to enter the portal.

The grad transfer DL from Fresno State played just one game with the Wildcats before suffering a season-ending leg injury.

Wishing him the best moving forward.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Are you missing the Big Ten West already?

Us too, so we ranked all 10 division champion teams ahead of this weekend’s Big Ten Championship:

Name: Inside NU
Content: First quarter*

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's all from Welsh-Ryan.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown on Harter: "She's someone I feel like can play multiple positions. She's smart, she's tough. We're seeing her confidence level go up. I think you're gonna see a lot of Casey Harter... there's a lot of great stories to come there."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown on Daley's foul trouble: "We need her on the floor, we need her firepower. She's also a defensive presence. Have to look on tape at the fouls, to see how we can clean them up... because she's too valuable to us and opens us up on the offensive end."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on Alana Goodchild playing the entire third quarter: "We're not a great three-point shooting team, and having her out there with three guards allowed us to stretch the floor."

Said that people will see her as "a legitimate threat from deep."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on cleaning up turnovers and transition defense: "Our turnovers sometimes are coming from trying to push the pace, which is how we want to play at times, but we have to make better decisions."

Shouted out Casey Harter for doing that.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown: "I was really disappointed today. I thought we had a great week of practice heading into today. We have to look at everything. We're fouling people just because we're out of position."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on taking steps to start faster: "We got to look at everything, from shot selection to defense.

"Great players make you foul, but we're fouling people from being out of position."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown shouted out Loyola's coaching staff for being "ready to play."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown: "Disappointed. The way we started in the fourth quarter is unacceptable, and something we have to address."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern presser to start. Joe McKeown at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Loyola 73, Northwestern 68

NU's comeback falls just short, and the slow start proved to be too much to overcome. The Wildcats drop their third straight, and have 5-1 Georgetown up next.

Name: Inside NU
Content: (yes, they needed a three there)

Name: Inside NU
Content: Walsh misses a layup, no foul is called, and that should do it.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Do you need a three here?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Fisher hits both. 72-68 Ramblers, and it looks like Northwestern will need another miraculous sequence to extend this one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern fouls, sending Alyssa Fisher back to the line with 12.4 seconds to go. If she misses one, NU will have a chance to at least tie.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Just when you thought it was over...

A FOUR-POINT PLAY FOR WEAVER! This could be a 70-68 game in a second.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Offensive rebound for Loyola with 25.6 seconds to go, and this one should be just about over if the Ramblers can hit their free throws.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott picks up an offensive foul with 55.4 seconds to go, and this should become a foul game real soon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A defensive breakdown on Lau leads to an and-one for Alyssa Fisher, and the Loyola guard makes this one a five-point game. She now has 16 points on the day.

Name: Inside NU
Content: PAIGE MOTT WITH THE SEAL IN THE POST FOR THE BUCKET! Terrific positioning from her, and it makes this a two-point game with 1:32 left. Timeout Ramblers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver with two free throws to get to 15 points on the day. 66-62 Loyola.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Big bucket from the Ramblers with 2:45 to play, making it a 66-60 ballgame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott with two big free throws. She's struggled from the field, but is 8-of-9 from the free-throw line. Big points from her.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Under five to play now, and a Galanopoulos three in Goodchild's face extends the Loyola lead to seven.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After Loyola gets points at the line, Weaver hits a floater on the other end. 61-57 now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After a Weaver steal, Walsh turns it over, which leads to a free throw for the Ramblers. Daley, who has four fouls, checks in for Pina. Lau is out of the game right now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver with the and-one after Loyola hits a midrange off a screen-and-curl. One-point game now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Harter with ANOTHER bucket. She still hasn't missed, and now has 14 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After a Loyola bucket, Mott hits (and converts) the and-one! It's a 54-50 ballgame with 8:30 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF THREE: Loyola 52, Northwestern 47

A 13-0 run from the 'Cats put them back in the game, and now Northwestern has a fighting chance. Alana Goodchild played the entire third quarter. 

Harter leads NU with 12 points on 5-of-5 shooting.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two free throws from Loyola end NU's really long run, and it extends the Rambler lead back to three.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley picks up her fourth foul while defending the post. She'll come out for Pina.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paige Mott REJECTED that layup. In a game where Northwestern's transition D has been shoddy, that was a really good sequence from her.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Alana Goodchild is on the board, and it's now a 13-0 run for the 'Cats! The Loyola lead is now down to one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver with a really nice rejection on the other end. She's heating up quickly.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Weaver with another three, and the Loyola lead is now down to five!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two straight threes for the 'Cats, as Lau and Weaver bury back-to-back triples! 48-40 Loyola, and a timeout from the Ramblers with 3:45 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Every time NU generates a little momentum, it gives up a transition bucket. Harter's fifth field goal in five tries and the ensuing fastbreak was a prime example. It's frustrating.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lau to the rack after a pair of free throws from the Ramblers, but Loyola answers on the other end. 44-32 LUC now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Harter has been automatic from the corner. She's at 10 points on the day, and still hasn't missed. 38-30 Ramblers through two minutes in the third.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's Lau, Harter, Weaver, Goodchild, and Walsh.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Second half is underway. Alana Goodchild is in for Paige Mott.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A huge rivalry week didn’t shake up too much in the Big Ten rankings:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Plenty of Wildcat talent was celebrated by conference coaches and media members.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALF: Loyola 38, Northwestern 25

16-0. That's the point difference off turnovers, and it's the one that has mattered most so far. NU is actually shooting better than Loyola from the field after a nice close to the half, but the 10 turnovers have hurt Northwestern badly.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Harter with another contested midrange, which brings her up to seven points on the day. She hasn't missed yet. 36-25 Ramblers with 1:22 left in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The offensive pace has woken up for both teams. They're shooting a combined 10 of their last 11.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Walsh with another three, but Loyola answers with one of their own. Ramblers still lead by 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Harter with a corner trey in a defender's face to cut the deficit to 12!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Galanopoulos now with 14 after another trey, forcing an NU timeout. 28-13 Ramblers with 6:49 in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Maggie Pina swishes a midrange J, but the Ramblers answer on the other end with a layup. 25-13 through three minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF FIRST: Loyola 21, Northwestern 10

The 'Cats have six turnovers already, and are shooting just 3-of-10 from the field. Not the recipe for success! Sam Galanopoulos has 10 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Casey Harter breaks the scoreless streak with a post fade. 21-8 Loyola now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It is 21-6 Ramblers. This Loyola team was 6-24 last year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Galanapoulos with a free throw and another three, and the Ramblers are now up 11.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Under five minutes to go in the first quarter, and the 'Cats trail 12-6. Loyola hasn't turned it over at all yet, while NU has committed three giveaways.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After Weaver hits a jumper, Loyola guard Sam Galanopoulos drains a three. It's 11-4.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Now eagerly anticipating a bowl game, this NUFB team has exceeded all expectations:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two quick buckets for the Ramblers, and three straight turnovers for the 'Cats, with Walsh picking up an offensive foul. 6-2 Loyola through three minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Really nice post feed from Daley, who leads Walsh for a layup to even things at two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We are underway, and the Ramblers get on the board first with a layup.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Starting for the 'Cats: 

Caroline Lau
Hailey Weaver
Melannie Daley
Caileigh Walsh
Paige Mott

Same old, same old. Tip is just seconds away.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We are live from Welsh-Ryan for some Wednesday morning (?!) action! Northwestern WBB takes on Loyola Chicago as the 'Cats will look to get back in the win column. Follow along here!

Name: Inside NU
Content: The ‘Cats are off to a rocky start...at least nobody can question their strength of schedule

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Per release, here were Northwestern's All-Big Ten defensive/specialist honorable mentions:

K Jack Olsen (coaches/media)
CB Rod Heard II (coaches/media)
DL Aidan Hubbard (media)
S Coco Azema (media)

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "This award is a reflection, first and foremost, of our players. This award is a reflection of the true character that's in this program, and in this facility."

Also shouted out staffers' work.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Also noted that NU "has to be the most physical team on the field" every game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Northwestern's identity: "Fundamentals and technique. When people turn on the film, they tangibly see a group that plays really, really hard. Uncommon effort. A group that plays together; that truly trusts one another, loves being around one another."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on recruiting: "When there's change like this, it's an opportunity to really take a step back and evaluate everything. We've done that."

Said there are "areas where we need to push the envelope and evolve" in a new CFB landscape while sticking to fundamentals.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on playing well in all phases: "That's how the 'Cats are going to have to win games: team football. At the end of the day, we're one team."

Says there was an "unwavering belief" among NU.

"That's what this team has proven it has the ability to do on a consistent basis."

Name: Inside NU
Content: In the second half against NIU, Northwestern was a vastly different team and one that heads into playing No. 1 Purdue on a positive note.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun, reflecting on when he first took over: "To say I was out of my comfort zone was the understatement of the century."

Noted the ability to "pour into" and "put his arm around" a team that needed it.

Name: Inside NU
Content: From never having coached at the FBS level to the Big Ten Coach of the Year, what a special arc it’s been for David Braun.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "This group just found a way to improve throughout the season. Certainly think that we're playing our best football right now."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun, speaking live on BTN, on winning Coach of the Year: "It's surreal. It's a credit to our players. It's a credit to this staff. It's a credit to the resolve of the entire program."

Said he knew the team "had the opportunity to do some special things" in July.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
BREAKING: David Braun has been named the 2023 Big Ten Coach of the Year!

Braun, who had never been a head coach at any level, took the Wildcats from 1-11 to 7-5 and a bowl game. He also won five conference games, including three straight to end the year.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern LB Xander Mueller made the media's All-Big Ten Third Team.

His 10.5 TFL and three interceptions led NU. No. 34 also racked up five sacks, 102 tackles and two pass deflections.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Jack Olsen did not win Big Ten Kicker of the Year.

His elite celebrations, on top of his 82.4% conversion rate, should have been enough.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern LB Bryce Gallagher made the All-Big Ten Second Team! His 110 tackles ranked third in the conference.

This is his second straight appearance on the award list, following a Third Team media selection last year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: In a few minutes on Big Ten Network, the Big Ten will be announcing some of its awards — notably Coach of the Year and All-Big Ten defensive players and specialists. Stay tuned for announcements!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern football offers a lot to be excited about, but don’t forget about the team’s NFL alumni.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Being ourselves and taking it one day at a time" Buie said is the mindset headed into Purdue.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "We treat every game the same. Whether it's Big Ten or non-conference," said Buie.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "I know we needed some energy," Buie said of coming strong out of the half. "I was going to make it a point to be aggressive. The plan was to score."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "He's seven-foot for a reason. You want to get him the ball at the highest point. It's really all about making a read," Buie said about his lob with Nicholson.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "When guys are getting double figures, it really shows our connectedness and unselfishness," Buie said. "Any of us can have 20 points."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "I didn't even know it was my hundredth start. But obviously, this place is super special to me and is a huge reason of why I cam back for a fifth year," Boo Buie said.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Not to make the game bigger than it is," Collins said is the message headed into Purdue. "It's a new year. They're new. We're new."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "If you look at our schedule, I think we've seen better teams than we have in previous years," said Collins of NIU, Dayton, Rhode Island. "I think we've tested ourselves well in those six games."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "We tried to stay more compact with our ball-screen coverage...I thought our guys did a really good job defensively in the second half."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "I've never seen someone distort the game in a positive way the way I've seen Zach Edey," said Collins, who elaborated that Edey is one of the most dominant players he has seen in his career.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "This is a game that our guys are really excited for. Hopefully, the fans are excited and the students are excited. I'm not sure I've seen a team as well-rounded at this point in the season. They're the best team in the country, no question," Collins said of Purdue.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Everyone knows how important Boo is to us and every team is going to try and take him out of the game... We have to develop the rest of our team," said Collins, who pointed out the performance of first-year Jordan Clayton.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Usually, when Ty is in double figures, it bodes well for us," Collins said. "What I love is that it came in different ways....He was a well-rounded player tonight and his defense was on point."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "He was able to not only have big scoring numbers but big assist numbers," said Collins of Buie's contributions.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "It can't just be the Buie and Barnhizer show offensively," Collins said. "That's why Matt [Nicholson] was huge." He also acknowledged how impactful Nick Martinelli's 11 points were.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie didn't feel great about how he played against Mississippi State, said Collins. But was able to make up for it tonight.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "[Buie's] little burst gave us the separation we needed. And Ty [Berry] was fantastic," said Collins, noting that he was the primary player on David Coit.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Great to see Matt [Nicholson] playing like that," Collins said. "He's working, putting the time in and it's paying off. He and Boo are connecting."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Really pleased with the win tonight." Chris Collins said. "Lot of respect over there in Northern Illinois," he said acknowledging Zarique Nutter, Xavie Amos, David Coit and Konan Niederhai.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Huskies were no match for Boo Buie and the Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Heading into Purdue off a blowout win sure is nice.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern takes down Northern Illinois 89-67. It seemed this game could go any way at the half, but the 'Cats were playing on another level out of the break. Buie had 16 points in the second frame alone.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Remember when NIU had a lead?

Name: Inside NU
Content: 83-61, Northwestern has stored this one away. Unlike the first half, the Wildcats have severely outplayed the Huskies.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie has erupted in the second half, adding 16 points in 13 minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson scores its first points of the second half on a pair of free throws.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Despite Northwestern leading 71-57, Xavier Amos is having a career day for Northern Illinois reaching a high of 23 points against the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Luke Hunger joins in on the scoring to make it 64-52.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern last had a double-digit lead nearly 17 minutes ago. But with 14:14 remaining, the 'Cats are up 61-50.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NU is pouring on the threes. Langborg and Berry have one, and Buie has two. Its 57-48, the offense has heated up again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie is hot out of the break, sinking a three to make it 51-48.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It took less than two minutes, but NU has restored its lead 48-46.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ryan Langborg sinks a three for his first basket of the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With two free throws Boo Buie joins Matt Nicholson and Nick Martinelli with nine points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NIU strikes first, 44-41.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Big Matt is in the midst of a strong game, with nine points and four rebounds for the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Xavior Amos has been lethal for the Huskies putting up 19 points. Meanwhile, Nicholson and Martinelli have both put up nine.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Despite Northwestern having a double-digit lead, Northern Illinois ends the half up one at 42-41.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer makes one of two, but the one-point lead is erased by the Huskies off a jumper from Zarique Nutter who has nine on the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's tied at 40 with less than a minute left, as Brooks Barnhizer heads to the foul line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After trading baskets to tie up the score twice, NU has gotten out to a 36-32 lead. Less than three in the first frame left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On an optimistic note: Ty Berry is back in the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: At 27-26, NIU has its first lead of the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Folks, it's 26-25. Five minutes ago the 'Cats had a ten-point advantage.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After nearly two minutes without a bucket (and two missed NU free throws), the Huskies add another to make it 26-22.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 26-20 with less than eight in the half. The Huskies are inching themselves closer to the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ty Berry fell awkwardly off a shot and has not yet returned from the locker room. Granted a free throw, Blake Preston took the shot in his place.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats lead by double digits thanks to an alley-oop by Blake Preston from Boo Buie and a three from Ty Berry. 21-11 with less than 12 minutes left in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A dunk from Ty Berry,a  three from Brooks Barnhizer and a shot from Nick Martinelli makes it 16-9.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Matt Nicholson has seven of NU's nine points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On its sixth attempt up the court, Northern Illinois made its first shot but still trails 7-2.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Takes a few back and forths, but Boo Buie puts the 'Cats on the board first, 2-0.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Huskies get the tip-off but miss their shot to start.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Follow along with the 'Cats' first post-Thanksgiving game, as Northwestern men's basketball takes on Northern Illinois.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Follow along as Northwestern men’s basketball takes on Northern Illinois.

Name: Inside NU
Content: “Many Northwestern fans considered 2023 to be a year worth fast-forwarding, circling Nov. 26 on their calendars to get through the throes of another miserable season. Instead, that day has arrived, and...few want this year to end,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up today's pressers from Champaign.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Wallace called the safety room "one of the deepest rooms we have on the team."

"Working to get each other better. Being joyed with your brother making the play."

Noted that that cohesion started in the spring.

Called Jaheem Joseph's interception "amazing."

"It's awesome."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wallace on getting extra practice: "It's kind of new for me having this bowl schedule. Not exactly sure what it's going to look like yet. Excited to be with the guys."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wallace on ST rebounding from last week: "I don't know if we changed that much. Every single week, we come in ready to attack each week. Come into meetings ready to learn and see what our coordinators have to say. Really just dominating what you're doing, and what's your role."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wallace on the special teams room: "I think it just goes to show the brotherhood we have as a team in general. Through the hardship we had this year. Special teams are a lot of the guys that aren't getting huge minutes. They're really a core of what it means to be a Wildcat."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Wallace on being ready on special teams: "I think for me, I don't have a huge role on the defense right now. I'm just making the most of my opportunities when they're presented to me. Trying to max out my speed."

Said he had the best speed last week on special teams.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Wallace on his touchdown: "It was insane. My sister's committed here for basketball. My whole family was here. It was ridiculous. I got the ball, and I was like, 'Can I return this?'"

Noted that his mentality was to not get tackled.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning: "Shoutout Ben Bryant."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning on the offense staying resilient: "It's huge when a big special teams play is made, when a huge defensive play is made. It brings so much life and momentum when it happens. We want to put points on the board that much more. We've got to take advantage of that."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning on watching the two-point try/onside kicks: "It was the mentality of, 'Anything can happen at any point.' There was no flinch in us on the sideline. We had faith in those guys, as they have faith in us, to make the play when it happens. We just trust our fundamentals."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Henning on beating Illinois as a state native: "Being from Illinois, the rivalry is just huge. Ending their season, that wasn't on our radar. We're focused on us, playing our best brand of football."

Gave a shoutout to Lincoln-Way East.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Henning on rivalry games: "It means a lot. Every game is big. Once it's for a trophy or a rivalry game, that much more."

Said he learned that NU hadn't had the HAT in two years, and "how much it meant to the older guys."

"It's a big deal."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning on Cam Johnson: "The receiver room, we push each other to be the best. We don't know who's going to make the play. He's played a lot football. He's one heck of a ballplayer."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning on making decisions to return: "It just kind of comes from coaches and schemes. Over the course of the game, might be a little more conservative than aggressive."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Henning on Bryant: "He's like another coach on the field. He's a field general. He takes charge, and he sees the field really well."

Shouted him out by wearing his merchandise pre- and postgame.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A.J. Henning and Garner Wallace also set to speak shortly.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up Johnson.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on where he wants to play: "Just somewhere warm."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on communication with Bryant: "I think it's sort of an unspoken bond. He sort of felt that I was in a groove. He just kept feeding me the ball."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Johnson on what he's shown: "That I'm able to play with the best of the best. I think that I've been able to put that on display week after week, no matter who we're playing against."

Praised the entire team, and both Bryant and Brendan Sullivan.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on offensive resilience: "I think that we realized that it wasn't Illinois stopping us a lot of the time. It was ourselves beat."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Johnson says that he's never won a rivalry game he's played in.

"I think it just means a ton. I've been through a lot of adversity in my college career. I think this team has been through a lot of adversity as well."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on his TD streak: "It's meant a lot to me to sort of see my ability to help the team win. Finding ways to help the team, whether that be blocking...or going out and scoring. I wouldn't trade it for the world."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on his career-best day: "It was definitely special. This is one of the best teams and favorite teams I've ever been a part of, especially in college football."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Cam Johnson now up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's all from Bryant.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on the HAT: "It means a lot for multiple reasons. It's so nice to go out like this to end the regular season. To get the HAT back is huge."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant on the second pick: "We had two go routes on both sides. I just threw it up to him."

Said Bajakian told him not to worry about it.

"It wasn't the end of the world."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on returning from the first pick: "That sucks. No one wants to throw a pick-six. We knew we were going to have another chance to go down and get the ball. Nobody had a sour look on their face."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on Cam Johnson: "Cam's a great dude. He works so hard. I'm so happy to see his success on the field. That comes with growth through our chemistry."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant: "We were just executing. We were throwing and catching the ball well. I'm really proud of the offense and how we executed today."

Praised the pass and run game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ben Bryant now up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun said the HAT was a "little bit lighter" and "not as dense" as the Dakota Marker, but that "both feel good in your hands."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on making a statement: "I don't know if the motivation came from ending their season. Today was a great step up for us in terms of the recruiting trail. We have to be great in the Chicagoland area. We have to be great in the state of Illinois."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on bowl game destinations: "Any opportunity to go play football with this group, we're gonna be thrilled about."

Called it a "spring ball come early" in terms of the ability to "help the entire program develop and move forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on resetting Bryant after the first pick: "I said the same thing that I said to all those guys coming off the field. 'Guys, it's on to the next.' We have a tendency to harp on what just happened. Let's learn from what just happened, and put it behind us."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "To me, the absolute best offenses and defenses are built in concepts that allow...coaches to get out of bad calls. That requires great teaching throughout the week, and a trust within your players."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Ben Bryant: "Offensive, we've done a great job of valuing the football all year long. A couple plays that he'd like to have back for sure."

Praised his "confidence" and "rhythm," plus "trust" among teammates. Stressed line of scrimmage adjustments.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "Isn't that how Big Ten West football... No? That's not it?" Braun joked about the combined 88 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on scoring 45 points: "Efficiency leads to explosiveness."

Mentioned double-move routes.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on his message to keep momentum: "I've gotten better at it. I still need to do a better job of removing myself rom the defensive play-caller mode."

Said he preached staying the course.

"This group continues to find different ways to win football games."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Cam Johnson: "He just embodied so many of the things that we value in this program. He's a warrior. Battles through nicks and bruises. Continues to improve."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On Olsen making from 45 earlier: "He's such a competitor. He's been so consistent this year. He's a master of his craft."

Also praised Will Halkyard and Hunter Renner.

Called the kick "absolutely critical."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the late delay of game decision: "That was a difficult decision. A lot went into it. His last kick just cleared the uprights. The trajectory of his ball was coming out a little bit lower than it typically does."

Mentioned that the team wanted to avoid a block.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on winning the HAT: "It's really neat. The two things we wanted to leave no doubt about were finishing the regular season the right away.. We wanted to leave no doubt that we wanted to bring the HAT back. I'm just so happy for that locker room right now."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "This team found a way to come home with the HAT."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "Just such a credit to our entire team."

Noted that parts of the defense "were not up to our standard," but that the collective effort was "winning football."

Called Ben Bryant and the offense "gusty."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun's opening statement: "Wow. What a game. Really proud of that group in there."

Talked about there being a "lot of reason to not have laser focus" after being bowl eligible, but NU staying the course.

"Winning rivalry games is never easy."

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun set to speak to the media shortly from Champaign.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats’ offense was humming all day, especially courtesy of Cam Johnson.

Name: Inside NU
Content: HAT secured.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 45, Illinois 43

A combined 88 points. A tip on a game-tying two-point try. And the HAT is back home.

Cam Johnson had a career-best day to propel the 'Cats, who have seven wins.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On the second try, Northwestern recovers! That's it!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun uses his final timeout.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Offside on the receiving team. Unbelievable.

They're kicking again.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern recovers the onside kick, and that's it!

However, there's a penalty.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun burns another TO before the kick.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Illinois will now attempt an onside kick. If the 'Cats recover, they win.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock's pass falls incomplete! The flag is picked up!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun calls timeout before the two-point play.

It's 45-43 NU with 55 seconds left.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Touchdown, Illinois. Paddock finds Washington on a catch and run.

Yes, this is real life.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock is *nearly* picked on first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Renner's punt rolls into the end zone.

Illinois down eight with 1:14 left, and 80 yards to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Uhhh, Northwestern is called for delay of game.

So, Olsen won't come out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter is stuffed on third. Olsen coming on.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On the Illinois 31, Porter gets one more. Illinois burns its last TO with 2:11 left.

Key third-and-8 now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter gets one, and Illinois calls its second timeout.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On fourth, Paddock is dropped by Anto Saka! Northwestern takes over at the Illinois 40 with 2:20 to go!

Name: Inside NU
Content: On a fourth-and-3 from the 40, Illinois calls TO.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Olsen is barely good from 45, but it still counts.

45-37 Northwestern with 2:56 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter hits the left side but is cut down, and Northwestern will send on Olsen.

Name: Inside NU
Content: From the Illinois 25, Bryant is sacked by Newton. Ball is now backed up to the 32. Third-and-16 for NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter is stopped by Jacas after getting just one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On third down, Devin Turner knocks it away, and Mueller has an interception!! The Wildcats are at the Illinois 26!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson has tight coverage on Washington to force an incompletion. Now third-and-6 for Illinois with 5:07 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Love makes one jump cut but is met after getting only four.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Love works the left side and is spun down after collecting a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant throws a deep fade to Kirtz, but he's intercepted for a second time. Terrific body positioning by Strain.

The Illini are down at their 6.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter hits a BIG hole and is all the way down to the Illinois 46. Gain of 22 yards.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant zips one to Mangieri, who astutely noticed the blitzing slot corner and vacancy. Pickup of seven.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning calls for a rare fair catch.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Rieman drops the two-point conversion. That kind of insanely weird game.

Still 42-37 Northwestern with 7:17 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On fourth-and-goal, Paddock locates Washington, left alone in the back corner of the end zone. It's now 42-37 Northwestern, and Illinois will go for two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Illinois' offense is staying on the field, down 42-31 with 7:18 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock MISSES a wide open Williams on a playfake. Unbelievable.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Terrific knockaway by Johnson to make up for the foul. It's now third-and-goal from the 1.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Turner helps wrap up Love, who's short at the 1.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Theran Johnson called for PI against Washington in the corner of the end zone, and the Illini will have it at the 2.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock is tripped up on the handoff, but keeps the ball. Loss of four.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jaheem Joseph walking off with trainers after that huge catch and run.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock rolls left and finds Washington with a ton of space. The receiver runs all the way down to the Northwestern 5 after cutting it back.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock hits Reiman underneath for five on first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Olsen's kick is fair caught at the 25, and Illinois finally held on to the ball on special teams.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern leads 42-31, and has scored 14 points in under 10 seconds.

This HAT might as well be crooked.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern forces a fumble on the kick return, and Garner Wallace has a touchdown!!

WHAT IN TARNATION IS GOING ON

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ben Bryant

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant keeps and runs up the middle for a Northwestern touchdown!

It's 35-31 Wildcats. We have a shootout.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Call stands after review. It is indeed a crucial first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bielema calls timeout. For now, it's first-and-goal from the Illinois 8.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant throws outside to Kirtz, who makes the catch and has just enough for a first down. However, this one may be coming back.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant is *nearly* intercepted on second down. It's now third-and-7 from the Illinois 15.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Gordon makes an acrobatic catch off a deflection for three yards. NU at the 15.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams muffs the fair catch, and Northwestern has it! The Wildcats are at the Illinois 18!

Name: Inside NU
Content: No idea what that was, but it was clearly busted. Henning wound up with the ball on what seemed to be a trick play, but lost yardage. Renner will now punt.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Himon swivels his way to a third-and-1. Key play here for the Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant finds Thomas Gordon for five on first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Henning's kick return is halted at the 23.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Paddock flips to Williams, who then throws to a wide-open Bryant for a 13-yard touchdown. The ex-quarterback keeps his arm alive.

It's now 31-28 Illinois after a good two-point try with 13:12 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Love bounces a run outside and stiff-arms Heard all the way down to the Northwestern 14. It's third-and-4 now for Illinois.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hagarty deflects an RPO screen, but Washington still grabs it. Loss of five.

Name: Inside NU
Content: To start the fourth, Paddock locates Washington, left open on the near side. He's got a pickup of 22.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
End of the third quarter: Northwestern 28, Illinois 23

This game has been back-and-forth all afternoon/evening, and that isn't changing anytime soon. The Illini are at Northwestern's 42 as the fourth begins.

Hold on to your hats, literally.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Love bounces a run outside but is met by Soares and Joseph. Two-yard gain.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Paddock works good timing with Washington on a stop route, and the Illini are quickly at Northwestern's 44 in two plays.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On first down, Love jukes out Gallagher en route to a 13-yard gain. Illini at their 40.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Olsen's kick is short from 45. Couldn't tell if it was deflected up the middle or not, but NU comes up empty. Could prove consequential.

Still 28-23 'Cats with 1:05 to go in the third.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Working out of the pistol, Nicario Harper shoots down the line to bring Porter down in front of the sticks. Jack Olsen is coming on to try from 44.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With Newton in his face, Bryant flips it to Porter, who gets seven. It's third-and-3 from the Illinois 27.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant checks it down to Tyus, who loses the football again. The ball is ruled incomplete, though.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The 'Cats have attacked outside the numbers well all day, and dial it up once more to Kirtz. It's another first down at the Illini 34.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NU spells Porter for Tyus, who hits the middle for three yards.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter keeps his legs moving on third down and has sufficient yardage for a new set of downs.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter makes one Illini miss but is two yards shy of the marker.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant keeps it again but scoots for only three. Northwestern at its 44.
